node.text:
A brief history of the Museum 👇🏽

Its beginnings date to the 13th century. It was rebuilt several times. Like many structures in Warsaw, it sustained damage in the Warsaw Uprising of 1944 .Reconstructed 30 years later 1974 ,it now houses Warsaw’s Center for Contemporary Art
The Castle currently houses the Centre for Contemporary Art, with its collections and temporary exhibitions, concerts, and educational workshops.The Centre has organized over 600 exhibitions since 1990
🌠

.
.
.

📍🇵🇱
I recently discovered that I enjoy museum tours and in general learning about different countries culture 💕🌏

snippet of the museum 👇🏽

The Warsaw Rising Museum was opened on the 60th anniversary of the outbreak of fighting in Warsaw. The Museum is a tribute of Warsaw’s residents to those who fought and died for independent Poland and its free capital.

.
.
.
#travel2023
#poland🇵🇱
